import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True)
    chart.set(xlabel='Delay (minutes)', ylabel='Frequency')
    chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='ignore')
    if len(data['distance'].unique()) > 20:
        ax = sns.boxplot(x='distance', data=data, orient='v')
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        ax = sns.boxplot(x='distance', data=data, orient='v')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x="origin", data=data, order=data['origin'].value_counts().iloc[:20].index)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which airports have the most flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
